The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, March 31 (PTI): The Supreme Court today pulled up the Centre for not appealing on important public issues like the gay sex row, but filing appeals on frivolous grounds.           
	This court is meant for deciding important questions of Constitution and Fundamental Rights. You do not file appeals on such important issues. You did not file the appeal against the Delhi High Court verdict on the gay sex row, the judge said while dismissing an appeal filed by the Centre challenging an order for an increment to a railway employee. Is this the way the Union of India behaves? he asked.                   
	 Chennai (PTI): Three directors of a firm have been sentenced to a years rigorous imprisonment by a CBI court for running an illegal telephone exchange. The fraud had caused a loss of over Rs 6 crore to VSNL and BSNL. The firm had linked the illegal setup with the normal telephone exchange and international calls were routed through it as if they were local calls.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The NSG will station stronger bomb disposal units at Hyderabad, Mumbai, Chennai and Calcutta for a better response in case of a terror attack. It will be acquiring the containment unit used in the Delhi blasts and also laser listening devices and shot gun spas, used to force open doors.                  
	 Toronto (PTI): A 21-year-old Sikh man in Canada was accidentally stabbed when a fight broke out between two neighbours over a noisy birthday party where he was a guest. Buta Singh Sangha died in hospital.                                                                                                                                              
